title: Gallery || Boogie makes Bayou debut
text:
Show All Slides Start Slideshow Next Slideshow 1 of 16 (Photo: Jonathan Bachman, Getty) 
DeMarcus Cousins made his Bayou debut with the New Orleans Pelicans in a 129-99 loss to the Houston Rockets Thursday night. 
Cousins, who was dealt to New Orleans from Sacramento late Sunday night after the All-Star Game, made his first shot as a Pelican, a jumper from the top of the key at the 11:28 mark in the first quarter. 
On the night, Cousins finished with 27 points, 14 rebounds, five assists, five steals and four blocks. 
Anthony Davis posted 29 points and nine rebounds as the two former Wildcats combined for 56 points and 23 rebounds in their first outing together as teammates. 
In all, Cousins and Davis scored or assisted on 67 of the Pelicans' 99 points Thursday night. 
Take a look back at Cousins debut in this CatsPause.com gallery.
